data.name: Creamy Tomato Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and velvety tomato soup that's perfect for any day, served with a hint of cream and spices.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and garlic, sauté until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the canned crushed tomatoes and vegetable broth, bring to a simmer.
Add sugar, salt, and black pepper, and let it simmer for 10 minutes to blend the flavors.
Reduce heat and stir in the heavy cream, simmer for an additional 5 minutes.
Use an immersion blender or regular blender to purée the soup until smooth (optional).
Serve hot, garnished with fresh basil and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese if desired.
data.modifiersForBase: Creamy and rich with a touch of sweetness
